<br>
I play both a Mage and a Beastlord (High Mage, 60, Highest Bst, 4<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Heres the difference between our pets.<br>
<br>
First off, Beastlord pets are their friends. They bond with their pet, nuture it, and the pets require the beastlord's help to survive. This is reflected by the Bst's great pet Heals, Hastes, Level Buffs, and Procs. The Beastlord can support it's pet for a much longer period of time without having to summon up a new one.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, a Mage's pet is just a lifeless Golem the mage has the power to summon up, there is no bond. Because of this, we have fewer spells to nuture the pet. We only have 4 total pet heals (levels 8, 20, 52, and 60), 5 Hastes (Levels 24, 39, 49, 54, and Ancient 60), and no other real pet related spells. Commonly a Mage can summon 6 or 7 Pets in a big fight, and lifelessly throw them away for a new one. We cannot keep one pet alive for too long, it just costs too much mana to heal it. Unlike beastlords, our heals aren't very mana efficient.<br>
<br>
A Mages Offense is about 50/50 between nukes and Pet. The more mages use their Rods of Mystical Transvergence (sp), the more they will nuke. <br>
<br>
A Beastlords offense is like 40/60 Between the Beastlord and the Pet. A Beastlord will use it's spells mainly to augment the pet, and to weaken it's adversary. However, Beastlord melee isn't to be discounted, there are some mean Bst weapons out there. <p>"History is just a set of lies agreed upon" - Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/unalilya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nalilya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beastling</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#FF9933>(9/28/02 12:53:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3675.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsdown.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I rarely tank</span><hr size=1> Mages should provide a certain amount of DPS and have their raid utilitarian function as well. I believe they have that with their pets, nukes, CoTH and mod rods (even if the utilitarian part is disliked, it is there).  <br>
<br>
Beastlords should be able to do the same in an equal manner.  With the SP line of spells and our Paragon AA I believe we have taken a step in the right direction for utilitarian use on a raid (whether we like it or whether it is enough can be left for another discussion).  <br>
<br>
Where we are hurting bad is in the DPS area.  We need a balance between our melee DPS and our warder DPS to give us that acceptable level of damage.  Mages do not want to see our warders outdamaging theirs and if that happens, there will always be hard feelings on the mages part.  Personally, I would rather see them leave our warders alone and give the Lord's in Beastlords a bit of melee upgrade.  <br>
<br>
Now, back to mage epic pets...One thing to keep in mind is that epics are not meant to be the &quot;be all, end all.&quot;  There are a lot of uber weapons out there that surpass all class weapons (beasts on the hurting side of this one for lack of class specific weapons..or having to see them all go to monks).  Now my big question...where is the upgrade for the mage's epic?  <br>
<br>
In my opinion, VI screwed up royally by making the mages epic a pet, with no hope of getting a better epic.  As the game progresses and melee folks are able to replace their epic weapons with better weapons, mages are left out in the cold.  Guess in a way I cannot blame them for being so protective of their pets.  <br>
<br>
I am just putting out rambling thoughts here.  Mages are not our enemies...and we are not mages enemies...we are all the victoms of SoE and I think we should try and remember that neither of our classes has the final say in what Verant will send down the pipes.  <br>
<br>
Ok, rambling off with no constructive anything added to the long discussions. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
